title: Jamat -e- Islami’s Azaz ul Mulk wins PK-17 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Jamat-e-Islami Pakistan Candidate Azaz Ul Mulk has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-17 Lower Dir IV by securing 25,124 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was an Independent Candidate Ubaid Ur Rehman who bagged 22,981 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 39.75 per cent.
